<p>## 11. PROCESS LOGIC OF EACH MODULE</p>
<p>### Module 1: User Management<br>**Purpose**: To manage library user profiles. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: User details (name, email, etc.). &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Validate and store user information. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Confirmation of registration.</p>
<p>### Module 2: Book Management<br>**Purpose**: To manage library books. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: Book details (title, author, ISBN). &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Add, edit, or remove books from the inventory. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Updated book list.</p>
<p>### Module 3: Member Management<br>**Purpose**: To manage library memberships. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: Member details (name, membership type). &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Registration and renewal of memberships. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Member confirmation.</p>
<p>### Module 4: Book Issue System<br>**Purpose**: To record book issuance. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: User ID, book ID, issue date. &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Check availability and update records. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Issuance receipt.</p>
<p>### Module 5: Book Return System<br>**Purpose**: To manage book returns. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: User ID, book ID, return date. &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Update status to return and calculate fines. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Return confirmation.</p>
<p>### Module 6: Fine Calculation<br>**Purpose**: To calculate fines for overdue books. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: Return date and due date. &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Compute fines based on predefined rules. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Fine amount.</p>
<p>### Module 7: Search and Reports<br>**Purpose**: To allow users to search for books and generate reports. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: Search criteria, report type. &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Query database for results. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Search results or reports.</p>
<p>### Module 8: Admin Dashboard<br>**Purpose**: To provide an overview of library operations. &nbsp;<br>**Inputs**: Admin actions. &nbsp;<br>**Processing**: Generate insights on library statistics. &nbsp;<br>**Outputs**: Dashboard view.</p>
<p>---</p>
<p>## 12. METHODOLOGY ADOPTED</p>
<p>The Waterfall Model was selected for its linear approach, allowing for meticulous planning and execution. Each phase follows a sequential order, making it ideal for projects with well-defined requirements.</p>
<p>---</p>
<p>## 13. SYSTEM IMPLEMENTATION</p>
<p>### Frontend Technologies<br>The user interface was developed using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Bootstrap for responsive design.</p>
<p>### Backend Technologies<br>PHP was utilized for server-side logic and processing.</p>
<p>### Database Design<br>MySQL was chosen for data management.</p>
<p>### Deployment Process<br>The software was deployed locally using XAMPP, enabling easy access for testing and use.</p>
