<p>## 22. SYSTEM TESTING</p>
<p>### Testing Strategy<br>The testing strategy integrates various testing levels: unit, integration, and system testing followed by user acceptance.</p>
<p>### Unit Testing<br>Tests individual modules for correct functionality.</p>
<p>### Integration Testing<br>Ensures modules work together seamlessly.</p>
<p>### System Testing<br>Verifies overall system performance against requirements.</p>
<p>### Black Box Testing<br>Focuses on outputs based on inputs without examining internal code structure.</p>
